1
00:00:09,733 --> 00:00:11,400
<i> Hi, Marj!</i>

2
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:13,400
<i>I didn't even get to hug you
last night because...</i>

3
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:14,933
<i> Paolo wouldn't let you go.</i>

4
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:16,800
<i> Because he feels guilty.</i>

5
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:21,367
<i>That he wasn't here when
we delivered the baby.</i>

6
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:24,333
<i>You probably think I told
some sob story?</i>

7
00:00:24,467 --> 00:00:25,733
<i> Why would I do that?</i>

8
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:28,067
<i>Marj's already vulnerable
as it is.</i>

9
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,500
<i>Thea, she doesn't need
to know that.</i>

10
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:32,867
<i> Let's not ruin both our lives.</i>

11
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,533
<i>Just stay strong, baby,
I love you.</i>

12
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:37,000
<i>Do you still have feelings
for Marj?</i>

13
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,233
<i>What kind of question
is that, Mom?</i>

14
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:39,467
<i> I already have Thea.</i>

15
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,000
<i> You didn't answer my question.</i>

16
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:43,467
<i>Why don't you just focus
on Thea?</i>

17
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:46,900
<i>You don't even realize how lucky
you are to have her.</i>

18
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:49,533
<i> Paolo avoids me even at work.</i>

19
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:50,833
<i> You have Edward, though.</i>

20
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,100
<i> He's still a Torrecampo.</i>

21
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:54,167
<i> But he's not the golden boy.</i>

22
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:57,533
<i>It just annoys me
that I met Paolo too late.</i>

23
00:00:57,667 --> 00:00:59,467
<i>Right when he was already taken.</i>

24
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:00,400
<i> It seems...</i>

25
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:01,533
<i> It seems spoiled.</i>

26
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:03,267
<i> My suspicions are right.</i>

27
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,867
<i>You and Edward
are having a baby?</i>

28
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,600
<i> This baby isn't Edward's.</i>

29
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:11,633
<i>If I'm eight weeks pregnant,
then this baby is Paolo's.</i>

30
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:25,933
Hon?

31
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:29,767
I've been trying to call you
for a while.

32
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:31,667
I think your phone was off,
I couldn't reach you.

33
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,833
Sorry, Hon, I had to work
overtime.

34
00:01:34,967 --> 00:01:37,500
No, I called your office
earlier.

35
00:01:37,633 --> 00:01:39,500
They said that after you
went out for lunch,

36
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:41,767
you never came back.

37
00:01:43,533 --> 00:01:46,267
Oh, we had an open house.

38
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,867
Tons of prospective buyers,
that's why I stayed out so long.

39
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,133
And there was no signal there,
so I didn't get your calls.

40
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:57,767
Wait.

41
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:58,933
What is this?

42
00:01:59,067 --> 00:02:00,767
An interrogation?

43
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:04,733
I've been working all day,
and this is what I come home to?

44
00:02:06,433 --> 00:02:07,533
Hey, Hon, hey, hey.

45
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:10,267
No, no, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

46
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:13,067
Hon, I know I'm asking a lot
of questions.

47
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,400
I'm just worried about you.

48
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:16,767
What if something happened?

49
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,767
That's all.

50
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,433
Hon, don't be mad at me, okay?

51
00:03:28,367 --> 00:03:32,733
You're the most beautiful baby
in the whole world.

52
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:34,733
Daddy loves you so, so much.

53
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:37,067
I will never let anything happen
to you.

54
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,800
And I won't let anyone hurt you.

55
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:42,300
Because if someone does,

56
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:44,333
they're dead.

57
00:03:44,467 --> 00:03:45,733
Hey, Love.

58
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,067
There's a line.

59
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:52,700
I'll be the first one throwing
hands if anyone hurts our baby.

60
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,800
You better take after your mom.

61
00:03:54,967 --> 00:03:57,600
Brave.

62
00:03:57,733 --> 00:03:58,633
Come here.

63
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:01,800
You know, I think...

64
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:04,767
our baby really takes after you.

65
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,200
Brave,

66
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,567
smart,

67
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,200
healthy.

68
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,733
Maybe even good at sales talk?

69
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:14,133
Then she takes after both of us.

70
00:04:18,933 --> 00:04:20,667
There you go.

71
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,033
Love?

72
00:04:28,733 --> 00:04:30,200
Is it okay if...

73
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:34,433
I don't go back to work
after my maternity leave?

74
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:38,233
I want to stay home for now
and take care of Jasmine.

75
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:39,700
Of course.

76
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:44,900
And Thea's been handling your
accounts really well anyway.

77
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:46,300
Why?

78
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:47,467
What's wrong?

79
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,500
Tell me.

80
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:57,167
I'm thankful Thea took over
my listings.

81
00:04:57,300 --> 00:05:00,400
And I'm grateful she was there
when I was bleeding.

82
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,600
But honestly...

83
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:05,667
I want to trust her completely.

84
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,467
I thought you two were already
friends?

85
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,300
Love, yeah, I'm happy
when she's around.

86
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:12,933
She makes me laugh.

87
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:13,967
But...

88
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:18,000
I can't forget
what she did to me before.

89
00:05:20,067 --> 00:05:21,733
Okay.

90
00:05:21,867 --> 00:05:23,400
So...

91
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,133
what would you like me to do?

92
00:05:26,267 --> 00:05:28,667
You don't want to give her
your listings anymore?

93
00:05:31,667 --> 00:05:33,967
I just want to be careful.

94
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:37,367
I know she's nice
when she's in front of me.

95
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:41,200
I just don't know what
she's like behind my back.

96
00:05:42,267 --> 00:05:44,600
So if it's okay,

97
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:48,067
maybe just give them to Hannah
instead, Love.

98
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,067
Okay.

99
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,667
I understand.

100
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,300
I'll take care of it.

101
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:53,433
Don't worry.

102
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:55,033
Thank you.

103
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,433
You're really good at
putting her to sleep.

104
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:06,533
Thanks.

105
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:07,867
Wait.

106
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,800
<i> We need to talk ASAP.</i>

107
00:06:20,933 --> 00:06:22,467
<i> It's very important.</i>

108
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,833
Wow.

109
00:06:45,967 --> 00:06:47,367
Those drawings are beautiful.

110
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,467
Let me see, Sweetheart.

111
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,900
Is this your assignment?

112
00:06:52,267 --> 00:06:54,833
It's for Baby Jasmine.

113
00:06:54,967 --> 00:06:59,267
I'm going to put it in her crib
so she'll be happy.

114
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:02,733
I'm sure she'll love that
when she sees it.

115
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:08,067
I hope my sister likes
what I made, too.

116
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,267
Oh, I'm sure she will.

117
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,167
She loves Baby Jasmine.

118
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:17,233
Of course.

119
00:07:17,367 --> 00:07:18,933
She loves her so much.

120
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:26,600
<i> Pong and I are leaving.</i>

121
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:28,100
<i> Wait, wait, why?</i>

122
00:07:28,233 --> 00:07:29,767
Hold on, why'd you stop?
You were still drawing.

123
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,667
Why, Sweetheart? What's wrong?

124
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:38,600
What if my sister gives all
her love to Baby Jasmine?

125
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:40,867
There won't be any left for me.

126
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,567
- Oh no.
- It'll all run out.

127
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:46,933
That's not going to happen,
Jobert.

128
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:52,300
You know, your sister,
has the biggest heart.

129
00:07:52,467 --> 00:07:55,733
She has more than enough love
to give.

130
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,467
Plenty for you.

131
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,433
Plenty for the baby.

132
00:07:59,567 --> 00:08:00,533
And..

133
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:04,433
she will never run out of love
for you.

134
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:08,067
Really?

135
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,533
That's true.

136
00:08:11,967 --> 00:08:14,833
Okay, I'll go back to drawing.

137
00:08:14,967 --> 00:08:16,467
- All right.
- I'll now focus.

138
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,867
- Focus, all right?
- I will.

139
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,100
Let's put this away.

140
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:23,733
- Hey!
- Oh my gosh!

141
00:08:23,867 --> 00:08:25,600
What's that?

142
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:27,333
What are you doing?

143
00:08:27,467 --> 00:08:29,933
Nothing, Yolly just has such
a wild imagination.

144
00:08:30,067 --> 00:08:30,967
Yeah, Yolly.

145
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:33,267
We're nice people, right?

146
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,667
Him? Oscar? Nice?

147
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,667
<i> I doubt.</i>

148
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:38,000
You better be careful.

149
00:08:38,133 --> 00:08:40,167
I'm warning you.

150
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,267
He's just like Sir Paolo.

151
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,567
Smooth with the ladies.

152
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:46,433
Just ignore her, well,
it's because...

153
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,767
What?

154
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:50,633
Nothing, I'm leaving.

155
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:52,167
Hey, hey, where are you going?

156
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:53,233
Stay here.

157
00:08:53,367 --> 00:08:55,200
- Okay, Yolly.
- Work's here.

158
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:57,467
I'll go wash the dishes.

159
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:01,333
<i>Marj, don't forget
what I taught you, okay?</i>

160
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:05,233
Just gently pat her back,
and Jasmine will burp.

161
00:09:05,367 --> 00:09:06,267
Okay, Mom.

162
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:09,400
My problem is her diaper rash.

163
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:10,267
<i> Oh my, Marj.</i>

164
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,200
Good thing you reminded me.

165
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:14,833
I bought some coconut oil.

166
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,700
It's from Quezon.

167
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:18,367
I got it at the market.

168
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,867
Rub that on her
before you put the diaper on.

169
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,133
So she won't get chafed,
poor baby.

170
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:27,967
Absolutely not!

171
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:32,533
I bought diaper cream
for her rash.

172
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:35,000
That's what we're using.

173
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,733
That stuff's too expensive.

174
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:38,367
This is way cheaper.

175
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:45,633
It's not like money's a problem
in this house.

176
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:48,200
Just because it's expensive
doesn't mean it works.

177
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:51,833
People have been using this
for hundreds of years.

178
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,567
Exactly, that's outdated.

179
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:55,767
Things are different now.

180
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:59,133
Mom, they're both fine
for Jasmine.

181
00:09:59,267 --> 00:10:00,633
Both are okay.

182
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:05,400
I swear.

183
00:10:05,533 --> 00:10:06,933
So fussy.

184
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:08,800
Excuse me?

185
00:10:08,933 --> 00:10:10,333
Fussy?

186
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:12,200
I'm just being a mom.

187
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:14,833
If you're used to being
careless with your kids,

188
00:10:14,967 --> 00:10:19,133
don't get mad at mothers
who actually do things right.

189
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:20,533
Oh, really?

190
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:23,433
Are you saying
I was a careless mother?

191
00:10:24,567 --> 00:10:28,900
Well, who has a kid she couldn't
even get along with,

192
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:31,500
so that child ended up
leaving her?

193
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:33,033
Mom!

194
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,900
Please, let's not fight, Mom.

195
00:10:37,067 --> 00:10:41,633
We all just want what's best
for Jasmine, we all love her.

196
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:44,900
So please, can't we just
get along?

197
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:53,000
Good thing you were able
to drop by.

198
00:10:53,533 --> 00:10:55,900
Mom's been waiting for you
for a long time.

199
00:10:56,033 --> 00:10:58,500
But when you finally came,
she wasn't home.

200
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:01,867
No.

201
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,067
I just made sure dad
wasn't around.

202
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,667
And...

203
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:09,700
Marj, I really came here
for you and Baby Jasmine.

204
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:12,367
Thank you.

205
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,267
We want you to be Jasmine's
godfather at the christening,

206
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,633
okay?

207
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:17,867
What?

208
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:18,867
Really?

209
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,367
Yes.

210
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:22,567
That would be a blessing.

211
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:24,467
I wouldn't say no to that.

212
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,500
There's no one more deserving.

213
00:11:26,633 --> 00:11:29,900
You're Jasmine's dad's brother.

214
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:31,967
You're like a father to her,
too.

215
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,067
How are you?

216
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,900
How are things
with you and Thea?

217
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,133
Is there a problem?

218
00:11:43,567 --> 00:11:44,800
Thea?

219
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:47,067
I don't know.

220
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,567
She's acting differently.

221
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:52,567
What do you mean?

222
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:56,467
When she came home,

223
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,600
I could tell something
was wrong,

224
00:11:57,733 --> 00:11:59,600
but she said she was fine.

225
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:01,100
Just tired.

226
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:04,567
But I know her,
I know when Thea's...

227
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,367
forcing a smile.

228
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,600
And...

229
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:11,200
I don't want to think she's
hiding something from me.

230
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:15,533
<i> Excuse me, Sir.</i>

231
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:18,133
Miss Thea says
she needs to talk to you.

232
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:23,233
Tell her I'm working on
something very important.

233
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:24,833
I don't have time to talk
to her.

234
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:27,200
Okay, Sir, sorry.

235
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:28,300
Thank you.

236
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:35,333
<i> Miss Thea.</i>

237
00:12:35,467 --> 00:12:36,567
<i> Sir Paolo's really busy.</i>

238
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:38,533
<i>- Sir.
- What the...</i>

239
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:43,833
Didn't I tell you I needed
to talk to you?

240
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:48,067
Sir, I'm sorry, she insisted.

241
00:12:48,233 --> 00:12:50,433
It's okay, Gemma, you can go,
thank you.

242
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:59,433
Why aren't you answering
my messages?

243
00:12:59,567 --> 00:13:01,933
I can't even call you.

244
00:13:02,067 --> 00:13:04,800
Obviously, I don't want to talk
to you.

245
00:13:04,933 --> 00:13:07,767
What part of that was unclear?
didn't you get it?

246
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:10,833
Maybe she's going through
something.

247
00:13:10,967 --> 00:13:13,667
Maybe she just doesn't
want you to worry.

248
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:18,133
I don't know.

249
00:13:18,267 --> 00:13:22,767
You know, Edward, I don't really
know Thea that well.

250
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:25,867
We only just recently started
getting along.

251
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:29,433
I'm still figuring out
our friendship.

252
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:31,100
But...

253
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:33,067
I'll say this.

254
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:38,500
We, women, sometimes don't admit
we're hurting...

255
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:42,000
because we don't want the man
we love to worry.

256
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:45,033
And sometimes we don't
want you thinking...

257
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:47,600
we're weak.

258
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:51,300
You can't push me away.

259
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:52,533
Not now.

260
00:13:53,967 --> 00:13:56,433
We only had sex once,
and you're already attached?

261
00:13:58,333 --> 00:14:00,200
Paolo, that's not my issue.

262
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:01,433
Then what?

263
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,400
I'm pregnant.

264
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:08,767
And you're the father.

265
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:18,867
And sometimes, even if I don't
want to admit it,

266
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:22,733
we're just moody.

267
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:26,967
So don't worry.

268
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:30,300
Whatever Thea's going through,

269
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:33,267
I'm sure she'll tell you
eventually.

270
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:38,467
I hope so.

271
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:41,500
I hope she doesn't have
a problem.

272
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:43,333
I hope...

273
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:45,000
she's not hiding anything
from me.

274
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:51,767
You think this is the first time
a woman claimed she's pregnant,

275
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:53,733
and I'm the father?

276
00:14:53,867 --> 00:14:55,833
I'm eight weeks pregnant.

277
00:14:55,967 --> 00:15:00,067
And you're the only one
I slept with eight weeks ago.

278
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,133
Edward and I

279
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:03,300
only recently started sleeping
together again.

280
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:06,800
Paolo, this is yours!

281
00:15:08,733 --> 00:15:12,833
How can you be pregnant?
We only had sex once.

282
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:15,100
Wow.

283
00:15:15,233 --> 00:15:16,567
Sorry, okay?

284
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:23,100
So should it take three times
before a woman gets pregnant?

285
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:24,833
Oh my God.

286
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:28,867
Baby, sorry.

287
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:37,000
Maybe you should go back
to your dad's private part.

288
00:15:37,167 --> 00:15:39,900
Because apparently once
isn't enough to...

289
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,467
That's enough!

290
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,000
Someone might hear you!

291
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:46,467
Why won't you believe me?

292
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:52,200
Fine.

293
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:54,200
If you're really telling
the truth,

294
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:56,100
I want proof.

295
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:57,967
We're getting a paternity test.

296
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,567
Fine!

297
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:03,033
You think I'm lying?

298
00:16:03,167 --> 00:16:05,600
You want to come with me
to the doctor?

299
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,267
So we can finally settle this.

300
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:39,833
Love!

301
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:41,100
Hi.

302
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:44,467
Have you eaten?

303
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,367
I'll fix you a plate.

304
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,767
Love, later.

305
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,800
Let's just stay here for now,
this day was just...

306
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:54,333
exhausting.

307
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:57,600
I just want to be here
with you and Baby Jasmine.

308
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:05,233
So I can forget about
the stress...

309
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:06,700
and everything on my mind.

310
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:10,000
Love,

311
00:17:10,133 --> 00:17:12,333
I'm sorry if...

312
00:17:12,467 --> 00:17:16,267
I've been neglecting you
these past few months.

313
00:17:16,433 --> 00:17:19,000
I want you to be okay.

314
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:25,133
I'm willing to do anything
to make you feel better.

315
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,900
Now that I've got
my strength back...

316
00:17:36,433 --> 00:17:38,300
let me make it up to you, okay?

317
00:17:51,933 --> 00:17:53,700
<i> It was nothing.</i>

318
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:55,133
<i>It was just a moment
of temptation.</i>

319
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:56,800
<i> It doesn't mean anything.</i>

320
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:58,700
<i>And it can't ever happen again.</i>

321
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,833
<i> No one knows.</i>

322
00:18:00,967 --> 00:18:02,000
<i> I'm pregnant.</i>

323
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:03,367
<i> And you're the father.</i>

324
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:08,967
Sorry, Love.

325
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,600
I'm just tired, okay?

326
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:11,967
Maybe next time?

327
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,233
Why?

328
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:16,300
Is something wrong?

329
00:18:16,433 --> 00:18:18,233
Are you having problems at work?

330
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,500
There is a big...

331
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:23,067
problem.

332
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,133
But, Love,
don't think about it, okay?

333
00:18:25,267 --> 00:18:26,967
I'll handle it.

334
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,700
Don't worry.

335
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:30,233
I'll fix this.

336
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:54,500
Weng, after you wash
and sterilize

337
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:55,700
Jasmine's baby bottles,

338
00:18:55,867 --> 00:18:58,667
just put them back
in the nursery, okay?

339
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,200
Yes, Ma'am Marj.

340
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,800
- Thank you.
- I'll head out now, Ma'am.

341
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:07,467
So how's the new mommy?

342
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,800
- Hi.
- Hello.

343
00:19:09,933 --> 00:19:11,800
What are you doing here?

344
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:14,233
Oh, Mom Regina asked me
to help her...

345
00:19:14,367 --> 00:19:16,633
plan her birthday charity event.

346
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:18,967
But our meeting's still later.

347
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:22,400
I just came early because
I wanted to catch up with you.

348
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:25,800
Me?

349
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:28,800
Nothing new, same as always.

350
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:31,567
The doctor said Jasmine
gained weight.

351
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:34,167
- Good.
- And Paolo's...

352
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:36,267
fine, too.

353
00:19:38,667 --> 00:19:40,800
That sounded a little forced.

354
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:45,167
Are you sure you guys are okay?

355
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:49,600
I can feel that my husband
has a problem.

356
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:52,900
Even if he's not telling me,

357
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:55,267
I'm determined to find out
what it is.

358
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,633
Of course, I want to help him.

359
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:59,133
Be there for him.

360
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:05,400
Back when I was the one
struggling, he supported me.

361
00:20:05,567 --> 00:20:08,833
So now, I want to do the same
for him.

362
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:13,267
I'll do whatever it takes
to make his problem go away.

363
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:16,533
You can't just make his problem
disappear that easily.

364
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:17,633
What?

365
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:22,067
What do you mean?

366
00:20:22,767 --> 00:20:28,300
Do you know something
about his problem?

367
00:20:30,467 --> 00:20:33,233
Well, isn't Paolo
under pressure?

368
00:20:33,367 --> 00:20:36,267
You know trying to win
back the...

369
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:38,633
accounts he lost at the company.

370
00:20:38,767 --> 00:20:40,400
So that's probably it,
I just think...

371
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:43,500
that kind of problem doesn't go
away that easily.

372
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,267
<i> I still have a client meeting.</i>

373
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,133
It might take a while,
maybe 30 minutes.

374
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:53,267
Just come back for me.

375
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,633
Thirty minutes, Sir?
I'll just wait for you.

376
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:57,367
No, just go ahead.

377
00:20:57,500 --> 00:20:59,433
I'll call you when I'm ready
to be picked up.

378
00:20:59,567 --> 00:21:00,567
Yes, Sir.

379
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:29,633
Paolo!

380
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:32,400
What is this very important
thing you needed to tell me?

381
00:21:32,533 --> 00:21:34,467
Why did we even have to meet?

382
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:37,667
I'm just excited for you to see
the lab test results.

383
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:46,233
It's still sealed.

384
00:21:46,367 --> 00:21:48,667
I haven't looked inside.

385
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:51,400
I wanted us to see the findings
together.

386
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,433
Just give it to me!

387
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:56,300
Let's end this nonsense
once and for all.

388
00:22:32,467 --> 00:22:33,500
See?

389
00:22:35,433 --> 00:22:37,800
I'm telling the truth, Paolo.

390
00:22:40,167 --> 00:22:42,233
Congratulations.

391
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:45,233
You're going to be Daddy Paolo.

392
00:22:45,367 --> 00:22:47,367
And we're going to have a baby.

393
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,767
No, no, no.

394
00:22:57,900 --> 00:23:00,000
No, this can't be happening.

395
00:23:00,133 --> 00:23:02,100
If Marj finds out about this,

396
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:03,900
it will destroy her.

397
00:23:04,033 --> 00:23:08,300
I promised her I would never
be like her dad or her ex.

398
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:12,200
So what are you saying?

399
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:14,333
You're going to deny this baby
I'm carrying?

400
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:16,467
You're not going to step up?

401
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,500
You're not going to acknowledge
my child?

402
00:23:22,133 --> 00:23:23,700
I love Marj.

403
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:25,267
Oh, come on!

404
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,367
This was one huge mistake.

405
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:32,033
One I completely regret.

406
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:34,867
And I'm not about to add to the
damage I've already done...

407
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,033
to my wife.

408
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:38,033
Oh? What about our baby?

409
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:40,100
What, you're just going to walk
away from us?

410
00:23:40,233 --> 00:23:41,333
Just like that?

411
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:46,233
I'll support the child, okay?

412
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:48,700
Just...

413
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:50,200
Just stay away from me.

414
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:52,267
And stop bothering me.

415
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:54,167
As for Edward,

416
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:56,933
you should leave him before
your belly starts showing.

417
00:23:57,100 --> 00:23:58,333
And resign from Torrecampo, too.

418
00:23:58,467 --> 00:23:59,500
What?

419
00:24:01,233 --> 00:24:03,467
You got me pregnant,

420
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,700
and now you want me
to lose my job, too?

421
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:08,500
That's not happening.

422
00:24:08,633 --> 00:24:11,900
You don't get to just
throw us away, Paolo.

423
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:14,033
My child has rights.

424
00:24:14,167 --> 00:24:17,567
We're not leaving
just because you want us to!

425
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,467
Whether you like it or not,

426
00:24:27,633 --> 00:24:31,133
the baby I'm carrying
is a Torrecampo.

427
00:24:31,300 --> 00:24:33,967
So you're going
to take responsibility.

428
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,967
And you're going to acknowledge
this child.

429
00:24:56,767 --> 00:24:57,667
Yes, son?

430
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,333
- Problem?
- Sorry,

431
00:24:59,467 --> 00:25:01,333
but they won't be able
to push me aside.

432
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:04,433
I'll destroy them first before
they try to control me.

433
00:25:04,567 --> 00:25:05,600
Thea's pregnant.

434
00:25:05,733 --> 00:25:07,900
Edward isn't the father.

435
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:09,000
I am.

436
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:12,267
I just happen to be attending

437
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:15,433
a Torrecampo charity event
tonight.

438
00:25:15,567 --> 00:25:18,167
That's where I'll expose
everything...

439
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:19,867
that happened between Paolo
and me.

440
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,567
That he's the father...

441
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:23,300
of my baby.

442
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:27,600
His wife and his family
will spit him out.

443
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:31,867
But how can I do that if you're
not being honest with me?

444
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,533
I was planning to tell you.

445
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:36,733
The truth is...

446
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:38,200
I'm pregnant.

447
00:25:38,333 --> 00:25:39,433
And he's the father.

448
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:42,833
Because of what you did,
you've only made our sin worse.

449
00:25:42,967 --> 00:25:45,233
It will ruin our family!
